##Dictation | boarded more than 100 flights in 24 hours, I in the aircraft to focus on the screening of passengers in key areas

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

I would like to say that at this point in the epidemic, it's not just our people on the ground, it's all of us.

Dictation | Sun Mingqin

Finishing | Ying Chen

On the night of January 28, I remember that it was a rainy night. I had just boarded a flight for quarantine and returned to my office at the Shanghai Pudong International Airport, there's a half-eaten box lunch that's been warmed up several times in the office. We didn't even know each other through a misty screen.

We were still on a 24-hour shift, taking over at 9:00 a.m. At this point, my colleagues and I have been working for nearly 14 hours straight, we boarded more than 100 flights that day quarantine.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Customs officers Sun Mingqin (first left) , Chen Xu and Li Hao focus on the passenger list before boarding the cabin analysis, a clear division of labor and work priorities

After we strip and sterilize the self-protection, my partner and I are off. There were six quarantine flights landing almost at the same time, while my assigned flight was parked in the far seat, carrying 26 passengers from key epidemic areas.

At that time, Shanghai Customs sent a lot of colleagues from other customs to support our check-in office and the Brigade check-in Office. Although everyone has a medical background, they are not familiar with our procedures. So in the beginning, in addition to explaining the process and equipment to them, we are to take "one old with one new or two new" approach in the actual work of their training.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Sun Mingqin explains how to use electronic thermometer for supporting comrades

On the way to the tarmac, I double-checked the equipment and equipment, whether the document form is accurate enough, and the transfer of colleagues to repeat the operation process after the plane.

Came to the far seat, see the flight slowly close to the bridge position, the far plane gangway quickly close to the cabin door, after getting off the rainstorm immediately wet our protective screen, once let us not see the road ahead. I instinctively shook my head, climbed up the gangway by experience, verified the information on the spot, and the airline signaled the flight crew to open the door.

Confirm the declaration with the flight attendant, hand over the passenger list, lock the plane to check the specific location of personnel, we appear in front of all passengers on the plane.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Customs officers prepare to board the aircraft for supervision

Although we usually have the work of boarding quarantine, but the frequency will not be so high as recently. Therefore, many passengers have not seen the full body protective clothing of customs officers. When we first got on the plane, some of the passengers would take pictures with their cell phones. Some of them are out of curiosity, and some of them may be used to send a micro-blog, processing our normal work into unnecessary "panic" . So, we will explain to the passengers patiently, ask them to put away their mobile phones. In the back, it's less and less. Basically, everyone is sitting where they are, patiently waiting for us to get to work.

At that time, each airline will arrange these groups as far as possible in the last few rows of the plane, one is convenient for us to check, two is also with other passengers at a distance. My colleagues and I trudged through the narrow aisles toward the back of the plane, the faces of the passengers as we passed. The passengers to be inspected are naturally very nervous, but not the focus of the epidemic areas of the passengers are actually very complicated.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The customs officer checks the identity of the passenger in the aircraft

The flight went well. Body temperature was normal. We had 26 people individually identified, temperature tested, epidemiologically investigated, and medically screened.

"What Day did you leave Hubei Province? "

"Have you lived or visited Hubei Province in the last 14 days? "

"Do you have other respiratory symptoms, such as fever or listless dry cough? "

"Your temperature is on the high side, I will re-test for you, please take off your mask temporarily, open mouth lift tongue, tongue pressure mouth closed. "

……

At one point, we were choking on masks, breathing in and out to reduce our oxygen consumption. All clear in 30 minutes. We'll tell the airline the rest of the passengers are cleared. At this moment, the front of the passengers actually collective stand up. I was subconsciously nervous.

"Can we clap? " In a passenger led off the plane rang a warm applause, a long time did not rest. Watching the atmosphere on the plane from dignified to relaxed, at that moment I was immersed in identity and happiness, and felt the need to work on the front lines. Our arrival eliminated the panic in the hearts of the passengers, so they can go home happy and secure.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wearing a day of protective masks, Sun Mingqin's face is full of scars

In fact, from New Year's Eve to the beginning of February, our check-in office and the Brigade check-in Office, the two front-line customs departments located at the port, are experiencing such high-intensity work. During that period, there were more groups from key epidemic areas.

Personally, I can't take a minute off during the peak days. My mind is completely blank. I can't think about anything else. Because do not drink water, do not go to the toilet, can only catch the opportunity to pick up a few mouthfuls of rice, it is completely by repeatedly through the quarantine process in order to give themselves "blood" , to stay awake.

In those days, every day from the beginning of the shift, the phone has been constantly ringing. "Hello? Customs? This is XX airlines. There are eight key passengers on our flight back from Tokyo. The scheduled time is 00:55. " The operator at our office quickly wrote in a notebook, at the end of the day, the book was full of flight numbers.

I ended up working 24 hours a day, came home from work, and basically had to stay home for a long time to recover.

Although very tired, but in the process of our work, the whole process is more and more smooth, the passengers are also more and more high degree of cooperation. And these days with the decline in flight volume, the focus of the region is mainly the individual-based, and we adjusted the scheduling, the overall intensity of work than before eased.

Through our effective screening, in our referral to designated hospitals, designated points of transport passengers, in fact, after the release is a confirmed case.

And in addition to the applause I just mentioned, there are many details that move me.

I remember during the temperature test, one of the passengers said, we were so careful that we didn't even dare to sneeze. We took the temperature twice a day for fear of causing trouble to others.

And a couple of six-and seven-year-olds. They had a fever in the regiment. The others were to be taken to a designated place as close contacts for observation in isolation. You'll find that sometimes children can be infected with adult anxiety. The first thing they say when they see us is, "Aunty, is Shanghai Safe? " And then they say, "I'm a little disappointed that I didn't have a good time this time, but at this point, I'm going to have to let it go. "
